Coming up next is the Science Fiction Radio Show, so stay with us.

24:05.060 --> 24:14.700
This is the Science Fiction Radio Show, a commentary on science fiction and fantasy. And here are your hosts.

24:19.440 --> 24:24.500
This is Daryl Lane. And Bill Vernon. People have been hearing about the wonderful land of Oz for over 80 years.

24:24.740 --> 24:29.420
It made its first appearance in L. Frank Baum's classic The Wizard of Oz, which came out in 1900.

24:30.360 --> 24:33.680
Why has the series been so popular, particularly the first book, The Wizard of Oz?

24:34.280 --> 24:39.160
We asked Fred Meyer, president of the International Wizard of Oz Club, why he thinks Oz has retained its popularity.

24:39.160 --> 24:51.840
I guess the idea of a little girl seeking home strikes a responsive chord to some people. And of course the search for wisdom, courage, and kindness are certain noble ideals.

24:53.820 --> 25:04.600
And a humbug wizard and so on also was attractive. But there's just something about them that strikes a certain response to some kind of people.

25:05.460 --> 25:11.460
And it's difficult to explain what it is. As a matter of fact, if you ask six different people, you probably get six different answers.

25:12.420 --> 25:17.660
Different ones will not even agree on which books they would prefer, of the ones they've read.

25:19.140 --> 25:22.840
It much depends on the circumstances under which you read the book, I suppose.

25:35.680 --> 25:40.840
We also asked Philip Jose Farmer, a longtime Oz fan and author of A Barnstormer in Oz.

25:41.620 --> 25:51.200
Of course there were many books written back in 1900 and afterwards about foreign lands or fairy lands.

25:52.220 --> 25:58.020
But what Baum did was to create a magnificent quest.

25:59.940 --> 26:11.900
And what you have Dorothy looking for a way of getting home, the Cowardly Lion wanting courage, Tin Woodman wanting a heart, and Scarecrow wanting brains.

26:13.640 --> 26:19.020
Now the thing is they all thought the wonderful wizard of Oz could give it to them.

26:20.540 --> 26:24.120
Well, he told him they would, but he put him through a series of trials.

26:24.420 --> 26:28.960
You know, first they had to go out and kill the Wicked Witch of the West.

26:30.540 --> 26:33.380
And I forget offhand what the other quest was.

26:34.620 --> 26:38.320
But the point was that they had all these qualities that they wanted.

26:41.580 --> 26:44.260
The Scarecrow was ignorant, but he was intelligent.

26:45.420 --> 26:49.620
Tin Woodman had a very tender heart, even if he didn't have a heart inside that timber.

26:51.440 --> 26:54.440
And the Cowardly Lion was like all of us.

26:54.560 --> 26:59.660
He'd get scared, but he was able to overcome his fear.

27:01.380 --> 27:04.400
But they needed some magical reassurance.

27:04.400 --> 27:18.300
And finally when they exposed the Wizard of Oz as a humbug, he still concocted physical devices, which were symbols of what they wanted.

27:19.420 --> 27:21.840
You know, he had the Cowardly Lion drink a pot of courage.

27:22.220 --> 27:24.860
Somebody had suggested he probably had that courage.

27:25.480 --> 27:34.340
Then he made a heart out of velvet filled with sawdust and put it inside the Tin Woodman's body.

27:38.520 --> 27:41.820
And he stuck... oh, okay.

27:42.780 --> 27:47.320
He put bran inside the Scarecrow's head and then he put needles in him.

27:47.360 --> 27:51.520
And he said his head was brand new now and sharp, needle sharp of course.

27:51.520 --> 27:53.100
And that was pretty fun.

27:54.180 --> 28:03.400
And having these physical evidences of things they wanted, they could seem to be very happy, although they'd have these qualities all this time.

28:04.120 --> 28:13.140
And I think that moral there, plus the wonderful quest in bound book form,

28:13.140 --> 28:21.180
is something that appealed to the heart of all the kids and the heart of adults too.

28:22.380 --> 28:26.120
The Oz series, delightful fantasy for children, clever invention for adults.

28:26.460 --> 28:28.980
It seems that these timeless books will be around for a long time.

